{"id":"anti-example-001","type":"pattern","fact":"Example: NEVER use 'as any' type casting - it hides bugs and defeats TypeScript's type system.","recommendation":"Use proper type narrowing, generics, or 'as unknown as Type' for test mocks.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"documentation","reference":"TypeScript patterns guide","date":"2026-01-09"}],"tags":["typescript","type-safety"],"affectedFiles":["**/*.ts"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-01-09T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-01-09T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"anti-runtime-state-in-install-dir","type":"pattern","fact":"NEVER write runtime or mutable state next to the code (e.g. $EASY_DIR). 'npm install -g' puts the CLI under a root-owned path, so non-root users get 'Permission denied' on write.","recommendation":"Store runtime state in Docker itself, a user-writable dir (~/.easy-proxy), or XDG state - never in the install directory.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"discovered fixing issue #5","date":"2026-05-18"}],"tags":["docker","runtime-state","npm","permissions"],"affectedFiles":["commands/**/*.sh","easy"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-05-18T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-18T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
